## Merge Requests — `<%= @project.full_path %>`

Manage merge requests for this project. All requests require a personal access token passed in the `PRIVATE-TOKEN` header.

**Base URL:** <%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>

**Authentication:**

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

---

### List Merge Requests

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

**Query parameters:**

- `state` (optional) — Filter by state: `opened`, `closed`, `merged`, `all` (default: all)
- `search` (optional) — Filter by title or description substring
- `source_branch` (optional) — Filter by source branch name
- `target_branch` (optional) — Filter by target branch name
- `author_id` (optional) — Filter by author user ID
- `assignee_id` (optional) — Filter by assignee user ID
- `reviewer_id` (optional) — Filter by reviewer user ID
- `page` (optional) — Page number (default: `1`)
- `per_page` (optional) — Items per page, max `100` (default: `20`)

**Response fields per merge request:**

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| `id` | Internal MR ID |
| `iid` | Project-scoped MR number (use this in URLs) |
| `project_id` | Target project ID |
| `title` | MR title |
| `description` | MR description |
| `state` | State: `opened`, `closed`, `merged` |
| `source_branch` | Branch being merged |
| `target_branch` | Branch to merge into |
| `author` | Author user object (`id`, `username`, `name`) |
| `assignees` | List of assignee user objects |
| `reviewers` | List of reviewer user objects |
| `web_url` | Full URL to the MR in the UI |
| `references` | Short (`!1`), relative, and full reference strings |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp |
| `updated_at` | Last update timestamp |
| `merged_at` | Merge timestamp (null if not merged) |
| `merge_commit_sha` | Merge commit SHA (null if not merged) |

**Pagination headers returned:**

| Header | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `X-Total` | Total number of merge requests |
| `X-Total-Pages` | Total number of pages |
| `X-Page` | Current page |
| `X-Per-Page` | Items per page |
| `X-Next-Page` | Next page number (empty if on last page) |
| `X-Prev-Page` | Previous page number (empty if on first page) |

---

### Get a Single Merge Request

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:iid" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:iid` — Project-scoped MR number (shown as `!N` in the UI)
- Returns `404 Not Found` if the MR does not exist

---

### Create a Merge Request

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"source_branch": "feature-branch", "target_branch": "main", "title": "My feature"}'
```

**Fields:**

- `source_branch` (required) — Branch to merge from
- `target_branch` (required) — Branch to merge into
- `title` (optional) — MR title; defaults to `Merge <source> into <target>` if omitted
- `description` (optional) — MR description
- `assignee_ids` (optional) — Array of user IDs to assign
- `reviewer_ids` (optional) — Array of user IDs to set as reviewers

Returns `201 Created` with the MR object on success.
Returns `422 Unprocessable Entity` if `source_branch` or `target_branch` is missing or invalid.

---

### Update a Merge Request

```bash
curl -X PUT "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:iid" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"title": "Updated title"}'
```

**Fields:**

- `title` (optional) — New title
- `description` (optional) — New description
- `state_event` (optional) — `close` to close the MR, `reopen` to reopen a closed MR, `merge` to merge the MR
- `assignee_ids` (optional) — Replace assignees with this array of user IDs
- `reviewer_ids` (optional) — Replace reviewers with this array of user IDs

Only the MR author can update or delete an MR.
Returns `200 OK` with the updated MR object on success.
Returns `403 Forbidden` if the current user is not the author.
Returns `404 Not Found` if the MR does not exist.

---

### Merge a Merge Request

```bash
curl -X PATCH "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:iid" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"state_event": "merge"}'
```

- `:iid` — Project-scoped MR number
- The MR must be in `opened` state and have a valid source branch
- On success, the source branch is automatically deleted if the namespace setting `remove_source_branch_after_merge` is enabled (default: true)

Returns `200 OK` with the merged MR object on success.
Returns `422 Unprocessable Entity` if the MR cannot be merged (e.g. already merged, no source branch).
Returns `403 Forbidden` if the current user lacks permission to merge.

---

### Delete a Merge Request

```bash
curl -X DELETE "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:iid" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:iid` — Project-scoped MR number

Only the MR author can delete an MR.
Returns `204 No Content` on success.
Returns `403 Forbidden` if the current user is not the author.
Returns `404 Not Found` if the MR does not exist.
